'''Yamaya no Taue Odori''' (山屋の田植踊) is a {{ill|rice-planting dance|ja|田植踊|12=draft|12=draft}}, a type of folk performance passed down in the Yamaya district of {{ill|Shiwa, Iwate|ja|紫波町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県|12=draft|12=draft}}. It was designated as a {{ill|Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property|ja|重要無形民俗文化財|12=draft|12=draft}} in 1981 (Shōwa 56)<ref name=":0">『わたしたちの文化財』紫波町教育委員会、1993rd year 。</ref>.

